{Another typical structure arises when after ...exf3 White recaptures with a
knight. In this position as well, the f5-pawn is a huge problem (with a pawn
on f7, the position would be normal). In such positions, White should try to
carry out the advance e2-e4. A typical way to prepare this advance is} 1. d5 $1
Na6 2. Nd4 {[%cal Ge2e4] Whit is ready to follow with e2-e4. After the
exchange of the pawns, White will enjoy a lasting advantage due to space
advantage and the weakened e-file.} *

