{Black has just played ...Nc8 with the idea of the driving the d5-knight away
by means of ...c7-c6. Afterwards, Black can already consider the advance ...
f5-f4. Therefore, White should play energetically. A typical reaction is} 1.
exf5 gxf5 2. f4 $1 {Very important move after which Black can never develop a
kingside attack. Meanwhile, White can expand on the queenside by means of
a4-a5 followed by b5-b6. A possible follow-up would be} c6 3. Ndc3 Bf7 4. Rb1 {
[%csl Rb7,Rc6][%cal Ga4a5,Ga5a6,Ga6b7,Gb5c6,Gh1b7] with a clear advantage for
White. Besides his good control of the centre, he is planning to open the
queenside with a4-a5-a6.} *

