{[%evp 0,11,16,0,-18,-54,29,23,59,59,12,9,28,29]} 1. c4 e5 2. g3 g6 3. d4 {
The most ambitious try for White. Black has 3 options here:} exd4 (3... Bg7 4.
dxe5 Nc6 (4... Bxe5 $6 5. Nf3 $14) 5. Nf3 Nxe5 6. Nxe5 Bxe5 7. Bg2 {White's
structure is better (see the explanations after 3...cxd4) and Black's minor
pieces are not very well placed. White should continue with normal development
as Nc3, 0-0, Bf4, Qd2, Rd1.}) (3... d6 {was tried by Anatoly Karpov several
times.} 4. dxe5 $1 {The best idea here is to open the position before Black
manages to play Nbd7.} dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 {[%cal Rb1c3,Rf2f4,Rf1h3] We reach a
queenless middlegame where White needs to play energetically. The structure is
quite comfortable for Black, but White has some dynamic opportunities. Black's
idea is to play Nbd7,c7-c6, f7-f6, etc.. The right plan for White is Nc3
followed by f2-f4 and 0-0-0. In some cases White increases the pressure with
h2-h4, Bh3 or Bh3 with a pawn still on h2. The weakness of the long diagonal 
(a1-h8) and the awkward position of Black's king gives White an advantage.
More details about this structure you can see in the theoretical chapter and
in "Typical Position" 1 and 2}) 4. Qxd4 {The understanding of this structure
is vital for the line. White has a space advantage and good control of
d5-square. There are 3 possible scenarios: 1. Black is playing d7-d6 and keeps
his c-pawn at c7. At that case White's typical idea is to put the knight on d5
and when the knight is exchanged to take cxd5 and to put pressure on the
backward pawn on c7. Another idea is to prepare c4-c5 at an appropriate moment.
2. Black is playing c7-c6 and d7-d6. At this case Black's pawn on d6 is a
serious weakness. 3. Black is trying to play d7-d5. This is the best scenario
for Black but it is really hard here, because White's pieces are controlling
"d5 very well.} Nf6 5. Nc3 Bg7 (5... Nc6 6. Qe3+ $1 $14) 6. Qe3+ $1 {Without
this move, Black will be just fine, but this check disturbs the harmony of
Black's position and White has an initiative in all lines.} *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
