1. c4 e5 2. g3 h5 3. Nf3 Nc6 ({The over-aggressive} 3... h4 $6 4. Nxh4 Rxh4 5.
gxh4 Qxh4 6. Nc3 Qxc4 {was chosen in Grant,J - Hector,J London 2016. Now White
should have played} 7. e4 $1 $146 Qd4 8. d3 Nf6 (8... Nc6 9. Nd5 $18) 9. Be3 {
, achieving a decisive advantage.}) ({Another ambitious try,} 3... e4 {, fails
to} 4. Nh4 $1 Be7 5. Nf5 d5 {This risky move is in the spirit of Black's
previous play.} ({The timid} 5... d6 {doesn't look like an attractive option:}
6. Nxe7 Qxe7 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. d3 exd3 9. Qxd3 {White had both the superior pawn
structure and the bishop pair in Tozer, P - Bennett, D West Bromwich 2014.}) 6.
Nxe7 Qxe7 7. cxd5 h4 8. Nc3 Nf6 9. d3 e3 $2 ({The lesser evil was} 9... hxg3
10. fxg3 Bf5 11. Bg2 exd3 12. Bg5 $14) 10. Bxe3 hxg3 {Petrov,N (2585)
-Morozevich,A (2659) Moscow 2019} 11. Qa4+ Bd7 12. Qd4 $18) 4. Nc3 Bc5 ({
Dubious is} 4... h4 $6 5. Nxh4 Rxh4 6. gxh4 Qxh4 7. d3 Nf6 8. Bg2 {Black had
no adequate compensation for the exchange in Lopez Ortiz, J - Odnorozhenko, E
Krasnograd 2018.}) (4... d6 5. d4 exd4 6. Nxd4 h4 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Bg2 Bd7 {
This was Goganov, A - Pasiev, R St Petersburg 2016. Here I prefer} 9. Qa4 $146
{, provoking the further weakening of the opponent's pawn structure:} c5 10.
Nb5 c6 11. Nc3 Qc7 12. O-O $16 {The lack of development prevents Black from
starting any attack on the kingside.}) 5. Bg2 d6 6. e3 Nge7 ({Giving up the
light-squared bishop is rarely a good idea in such positions:} 6... Bg4 7. h3
Bxf3 8. Bxf3 Qd7 9. a3 Nf6 10. b4 Bb6 11. Bg2 $16 {Jumabayev,R - Egorov,E
Astana 2014}) 7. O-O Bb6 {We have been following the game Flores, D - Bachmann,
A Asuncion 2015. At this point White could have exploited the drawbacks of the
early h7-h5 with} 8. d4 $1 $146 exd4 (8... Bg4 9. d5 Nb8 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Bxf3
h4 12. g4 {is clearly better for White - Black lacks any active counterplay.})
9. exd4 Bg4 {The pin looks annoying, but White can deal with it.} 10. Re1 Nxd4
{Black grabs the central pawn, but it costs him 2 tempi.} ({Hardly better is} 
10... Qd7 11. Nd5 O-O-O 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Nxb6+ axb6 14. Qxf3 $16) 11. Nd5 Ne6
12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 $36 {White's development advantage and the powerful Bg2
provide more than sufficient compensation for the pawn.} *

