[PlyCount "0"]

{Botvinnik System The idea of putting the pawn on e4 was invented by Mikhail
Botvinnik. White wants to play on the kingside as well by pushing
f2-f4-sometimes even f4-f5. In this structure, the knight on d5 is also very
well protected. The drawbacks of this system are that now the d4-square is
weakened and can be occupied by Black's knight and White's bishop is
temporarily closed. White usually plays on both flangs here, trying to combine
f2-f4 and d2-d4 ideas.}  *

