be ignored:} 15. Rae1 $1 $146 Bf3 16. d4 Ne6 17. dxe5 Nxg5 18. Qxg5 Bxg2 19.
Kxg2 Bxe5 20. Qe7 $14 {White manages to liquidate into a comfortable endgame,
where his pieces are more active and Black's queenside pawns are somewhat
vulnerable.}) (13... Rf7 14. b5 Nd8 {, as in Perez Fungueiro,M - Moreno Ruiz,J
Lorca 2005 can also be well met by} 15. Bxd8 $146 Rxd8 16. Ne3 Bh3 17. Bxb7
Bxf1 18. Rxf1 $14 {with more or less the same issues for Black.}) 14. b5 Nd8
15. Bxd8 {The most concrete way of handling the position.} Rxd8 16. Ne3 Bh3 {
Black's idea is to liquidate the strong Bg2, to make White's king vulnerable.}
(16... c6 17. Nxf5 gxf5 18. Qg5 Nf6 19. Rab1 $36 {The pressure along the
